The paper discusses the security issues of machine learning in IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes new techniques built upon adversarial machine learning, which involves the use of deep neural networks, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attacks discussed in the paper are related to wireless communications, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a defense mechanism to improve the security of IoT networks, which involves system design and control (cs.SY).
